data.enText: any plant without leaves, flowers or green colouring, usually growing on other plants or on decaying matter. Mushrooms and mildew are both fungi .
a covering of mould or a similar fungus , for example on a plant or wall

tr: an organism of the kingdom Fungi lacking chlorophyll and feeding on organic matter
ranging from unicellular or multicellular organisms to spore-bearing syncytia

value.def: A fungus is a plant that has no flowers, leaves, or green colouring, such as a mushroom or a toadstool. Other types of fungus such as mould are extremely small and look like a fine powder.
